page.content: Then, at 10.10 a.m., he travels to Thornhill. After visiting Thornhill at 10.25, he then called to advise a householder on methods of controlling a persistent infestation of black ants. At 10.40, Mr. Seddon removed a wasps nest from a neighbouring house which was on a roofing truss in an attic. After that, at 10.50, he checked the loft space of another Thornhill property in order to establish the source of unusual scratching noises. The problem was being caused by roosting starlings (though there was no nest) and he advised the householder on the need to block the access point.
